definitions.definition: To distort (an image ) by projecting it onto a surface at an angle , which for example causes a square to look like a trapezoid .
To double the cost price in order to determine the retail price; to apply a markup of 100%.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To distort (an image ) by projecting it onto a surface at an angle , which for example causes a square to look like a trapezoid .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , retail ) To double the cost price in order to determine the retail price; to apply a markup of 100%.
